## 2. Neo4j: Labeled-Property Graph Model

```
Node: (:Person {name: "Alice", age: 30})
Relationship: -[:KNOWS {since: 2020}]->
Node: (:Person {name: "Bob"})
```

### Cypher Query Language — Core Clauses
| Clause | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `MATCH` | Pattern matching — find nodes/relationships |
| `WHERE` | Filter conditions |
| `RETURN` | Specify output |
| `CREATE` | Create nodes/relationships |
| `MERGE` | Create if not exists, match if exists |
| `SET` | Update properties |
| `DELETE` / `DETACH DELETE` | Remove nodes/relationships |
| `WITH` | Chain query stages |
| `COLLECT` | Aggregate into list |
| `UNWIND` | Expand list into rows |

### Essential Cypher Patterns
```cypher
-- Match all persons who know each other
MATCH (a:Person)-[:KNOWS]->(b:Person)
RETURN a.name, b.name

-- Create a relationship
MERGE (a:Person {name: "Alice"})
MERGE (b:Person {name: "Bob"})
MERGE (a)-[:KNOWS {since: 2024}]->(b)

-- Count relationships per node
MATCH (p:Person)-[:KNOWS]->()
RETURN p.name, COUNT(*) AS connections
ORDER BY connections DESC

-- Import CSV
LOAD CSV WITH HEADERS FROM 'file:///data.csv' AS row
CREATE (:Entity {id: row.id, name: row.name})
```

